The speaker is about to begin the process of opening their input file, which in this case, is the 'Tiny Shakespeare' dataset. This dataset contains all of the works of Shakespeare in a single file, and they will be using it to train a language model, teaching it to predict what character is likely to come next in a given sequence from the dataset. Opening the "input" refers to loading the dataset into their program or code in order to begin the process of training the language model.